{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"findSourceByID"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"sourceID"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"text":"SourceRef","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceRef","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib9SourceRefV"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is a programmer error to attempt to look up a non-existent source."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"More specifically: source IDs can be reissued after a source has been","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"destroyed and therefore it is never valid to use this function with a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"source ID which may have already been removed.  An example is when","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"scheduling an idle to run in another thread with [func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.idle_add"},{"type":"text","text":"]: the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"idle may already have run and been removed by the time this function","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"is called on its (now invalid) source ID.  This source ID may have"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"been reissued, leading to the operation being performed against the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"wrong source."}]}]}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"role":"symbol","externalID":"s:4GLib19MainContextProtocolPAAE14findSourceByID06sourceH0AA0F3RefVSgSi_tF::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib14MainContextR